@node Intro "OverView"


     This is a restricted shareware version of FinalTable, with many features removed or disabled.  The full version of FinalTable is free when you @{"register this version" link reg} for only Ł3.50.

     FinalTable is not just a macro, but a MACRO and full program to add the facility to create tables in FinalWriter, a feature that the program does not currently support.

     I feel that the program is better than the other current release, "Final Tables", which forces the user to enter each cell into a requester individually.  FinalTable allows the widths, heights of columns and rows to be edited on-screen and then the fonts, sizes, titles, etc... to be changed and viewed at the same time.

     To see how good and powerful the program is, just use it!

@endnode

@node install "Installation"


     Installation is VERY simple:

                    - Copy the file FinalTable.Rexx wherever you wish to on
                      your hard drive.  (normally in FWMacros directory)

                    - Copy the file FinalTable onto your hard drive also.

                    - Copy CanDo.library into your LIBS directory

                    - ASSIGN FinalTable: to the directory where the file
                      FinalTable is, i.e: put this line in your user-startup
                      file:
 
                              ASSIGN FinalTable:  <dir where FinalTable is>

     And that's that!  


                                @{"Using FinalTable" link use}

@endnode

@node use "Using The Program"


     VERY BRIEF DOCUMENTATION FOR EARLY RELEASE OF FINALTABLE:-


                Load FinalWriter

                Type in the text you wish to make into a table, separating
                each item with commas, e.g:

                              Name,Price,Comment
                              BMW,Ł300,Wow!
                              Ford,Ł200,Great
                              Granada,Ł500,Rip Off

                Highlight the text using the left mouse button

                Run the Arexx Script 'FinalTable.rexx', either from the 'User'
                menu in FinalWriter or by assigning a button to it.  (see
                your FinalWriter manual)


     You have then entered the main table editing window.

     Move around the table using the cursor keys.  Press RETURN on a cell
     to alter the column/row width of the current column or row.  Alter these
     using the cursor keys also.

     Use the menus or shortcut keys to change justification / type style.

     The buttons on the left dictate what gets changed when a new justification
     or typestyle is selected - R = whole row,  C = Whole Column,  A = All table
     S = Single Cell

     Shortcut keys for those buttons are R,C,A and S  (wow!)

     Press Opts to change no. rows, columns, whether there's a border and
     gridlines and to change fonts  (sorry - not a proper font requester in the
     unregistered version and only one font for the whole table and one font
     for the whole title! - WHY NOT @{"register?" link reg}

     Press Generate to create the table and then 'Use Document' from the preview
     screen to put the table into your FinalWriter document.

     You will then have to input the width and height of the table (in ruler units)


     The rest, as they say, is history!


     Good LUCK - Hope the program is of use.  If you do find it useful, then why
     not pay Ł3.50 to @{"register" link reg} and receive the full version of 
     FinalTable, which is SO MUCH BETTER, including Text Editing, Border Types, 
     MultiFont, MultiHeader and LOADS more features to make your tables even
     better!

@endnode


